climbs.name: Cyanide
climbs.fa: Howard Doyle, Phil Sena, and Paul Muehl 1984

content.description: start at the bottom of the small ledge next to a dirt mound, climb up with little protection to a nice pod about 35 feet up. Place good gear then climb the small overhanging finger crack.(crux)Then its about 20 feet of easy climbing to the top with an optional gear placement. Descent: you can either walk of or sling a big horn with your rope and rappel.
content.location: walk about 25 yards past End Pin. If you turn around and face End Pin it will be on the left side. It is to the right of Bushwhacker. look for and overhang with a small pod below it.

content.description: Wall in the gully on the turn around in the Tenpins/Switchbacks.
